## Auto-Fix and Suggestion System

### Level 1: Auto-Fix (No Confirmation Required)

**Safe, deterministic fixes applied automatically:**

```
# Code formatting
Bash(command="dotnet format")           # C#
Bash(command="black src/")              # Python
Bash(command="prettier --write src/")   # JavaScript/TypeScript

# Import organization
Bash(command="dotnet format --no-restore")  # C# using statements
Bash(command="isort src/")                  # Python imports
Bash(command="eslint --fix src/")           # JavaScript imports

# Remove unused imports
# (Language-specific linters handle this)

# Fix naming conventions
# (Some linters can auto-fix PascalCase/camelCase)

Report: "Auto-fixed {count} formatting/linting violations"
```

### Level 2: Suggest Complex Fixes (With Code Generation)

**Generate fixes, present to developer for approval:**

#### Example 1: Magic Number Extraction

```
DETECTED:
File: src/Services/OrderService.cs:42
Code: if (order.Total > 1000) { ApplyFreeShipping(); }
Issue: Magic number 1000

GENERATE FIX:
const_name = "FREE_SHIPPING_THRESHOLD"
const_value = "1000m"
const_location = "class OrderService (top)"

suggested_code = f"""
private const decimal {const_name} = {const_value};
...
if (order.Total > {const_name}) {{ ApplyFreeShipping(); }}
"""

AskUserQuestion:
Question: "Magic number detected: 1000 in line 42. Apply suggested fix?"
Header: "Auto-fix"
Options:
  - "Yes, apply fix"
  - "No, keep as is"
  - "Show diff first"
multiSelect: false

IF answer == "Yes":
    # Apply fix using Edit tool
    Edit(file_path="src/Services/OrderService.cs",
         old_string="public class OrderService\n{",
         new_string=f"public class OrderService\n{{\n    private const decimal {const_name} = {const_value};")

    Edit(file_path="src/Services/OrderService.cs",
         old_string="if (order.Total > 1000)",
         new_string=f"if (order.Total > {const_name})")

    Report: "Applied fix: Extracted magic number to constant"

IF answer == "Show diff first":
    # Show diff, then ask again
```

