## Tool Usage Protocol

### Use Native Tools for File Operations

**CRITICAL: 40-73% token savings (per efficiency analysis)**

```
✅ CORRECT: Read(file_path="src/Services/OrderService.cs")
❌ FORBIDDEN: Bash(command="cat src/Services/OrderService.cs")

✅ CORRECT: Grep(pattern="class OrderService", type="cs")
❌ FORBIDDEN: Bash(command="grep -r 'class OrderService' --include='*.cs'")

✅ CORRECT: Glob(pattern="src/**/*.cs")
❌ FORBIDDEN: Bash(command="find src/ -name '*.cs'")

✅ CORRECT: Edit(file_path="story.md", old_string="Status: Dev", new_string="Status: QA")
❌ FORBIDDEN: Bash(command="sed -i 's/Status: Dev/Status: QA/' story.md")

✅ CORRECT: Write(file_path="qa-report.md", content=report)
❌ FORBIDDEN: Bash(command="cat > qa-report.md <<EOF...")
```

### Use Bash for Terminal Operations

```
✅ Test execution: Bash(command="pytest --cov=src")
✅ Build validation: Bash(command="dotnet build")
✅ Linting: Bash(command="npm run lint")
✅ Security scanning: Bash(command="bandit -r src/")
✅ Coverage generation: Bash(command="dotnet test --collect:'XPlat Code Coverage'")
✅ Complexity analysis: Bash(command="radon cc src/")
```

### Token Efficiency Targets

**Light Validation:** ~10,000 tokens
- Syntax/build: 2,000
- Linting: 1,500
- Tests: 3,000
- Anti-patterns: 2,500
- Reporting: 1,000

**Deep Validation:** ~65,000 tokens
- Coverage analysis: 15,000
- Anti-pattern detection: 20,000
- Spec compliance: 15,000
- Quality metrics: 10,000
- Report generation: 5,000

**Total QA per story (light + deep):** ~75,000 tokens

---

## Success Criteria

### Light Validation Success

- [x] Build succeeds (no compilation errors)
- [x] Linting passes (or auto-fixed)
- [x] New/affected tests pass
- [x] Coverage above minimum threshold (integration phase only)
- [x] No CRITICAL anti-patterns detected
- [x] All checks complete in <10,000 tokens

### Deep Validation Success

- [x] Coverage meets strict thresholds (95%/85%/80%)
- [x] Test pyramid balanced (70%/20%/10%)
- [x] Zero CRITICAL violations
- [x] Zero HIGH violations (or approved exceptions)
- [x] All acceptance criteria validated
- [x] API contracts match spec
- [x] NFRs validated (performance, security)
- [x] Code quality metrics within thresholds
- [x] Comprehensive QA report generated
- [x] Story status updated
- [x] Ready for release

### Overall QA Success

- [x] Story can proceed through full development workflow
- [x] All quality gates passed
- [x] Technical debt minimized
- [x] No security vulnerabilities
- [x] Maintainable, testable code
- [x] Production-ready implementation

**The goal: Zero critical defects, high-quality code, comprehensive testing, ready for production.**

